---
description: Use the zeroheight design system as the source of truth for UI work
alwaysApply: false
---

When building, modifying, or reviewing UI — components, pages, styles, theming,
or anything touching color, spacing, typography, radius, shadow, or motion — treat
the connected zeroheight styleguide as the source of truth, and consult it via the
`zeroheight` MCP server before writing code.

- Never invent component names, prop names, variants, token names, or token values —
  look them up in the styleguide first.
- If a component, prop, pattern, or token is not documented in the styleguide, say so
  explicitly rather than guessing.
- zeroheight documents the design intent and usage rules ("which component and when");
  follow any Storybook links it surfaces for the runtime API (exact props, types, and
  runnable examples) rather than going to Storybook first.
